# **1) Add Light/Dark theme toggle to your existing Advanced app**

**A) Add the button (inside the top**

**.toolbar**

**)**

Search in your file for the toolbar buttons and insert this anywhere in that group:

<button class="btn" id="btnTheme">ðŸŒ“ Theme</button>

**B) Add the light palette CSS (anywhere inside**Â 
**<style>...</style>**
**, after the**Â 
**:root{...}**
Â **block)**

/* Light theme palette overrides */
body[data-theme="light"]{
--bg:#f6f8fb;
--panel:#ffffff;
--muted:#49606f;
--text:#0a1620;
--accent:#0e7ad1;
--accent-2:#0e9d7a;
--chip:#f0f3f7;
--chip-active:#e5f2ff;
--border:#dbe3ea;
--danger:#c62828;
--ok:#2e7d32;
--warn:#a86d00;
}
body[data-theme="light"] body,
body[data-theme="light"] .btn{ background-image:none; }
body[data-theme="light"] .card,
body[data-theme="light"] .toolbar,
body[data-theme="light"] .filters,
body[data-theme="light"] #bundlePane{ box-shadow:0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.06); }
body[data-theme="light"] .panel-body .block{ background:#fbfdff; }

**C) Add the JS (near the bottom, after other handlers but before**Â 
**boot();**
**)**

<script>
/* Theme toggle */
(function(){
const KEY='lcu.theme';
function setTheme(t){ document.body.dataset.theme=t; try{localStorage.setItem(KEY,t);}catch{} }
function getTheme(){ try{ return localStorage.getItem(KEY)||'dark'; }catch{ return 'dark'; } }
window.initTheme = function(){ setTheme(getTheme()); };
window.toggleTheme = function(){
const next = (document.body.dataset.theme==='light') ? 'dark' : 'light';
setTheme(next);
toast(`Theme: ${next}`);
};
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', ()=>{
const b=document.getElementById('btnTheme');
if(b){ b.addEventListener('click', toggleTheme); }
});
})();
</script>

**D) Call**

**initTheme()**

**once on boot**

Inside your existing boot() function (top or bottom is fine), add:

initTheme();

Thatâ€™s it. Your Advanced app now remembers Light/Dark in localStorage and toggles instantly.